#dropping the customerID column
df.drop('customerID',axis=1,inplace=True)
In [23]:
#will incarporate changes in categorical variable with cosmetic change
df['gender'].replace(['Female','Male'],[0,1],inplace=True)
df['Partner'].replace(['Yes','No'],[1,0],inplace=True)
df['Dependents'].replace(['No','Yes'],[0,1],inplace=True)
df['PhoneService'].replace(['No','Yes'],[0,1],inplace=True)
df['MultipleLines'].replace(['No phone service', 'No', 'Yes'],[0,0,1],inplace=True)
df['InternetService'].replace(['DSL', 'Fiber optic','No'],[1,2,0],inplace=True)
df['OnlineSecurity'].replace(['No','Yes','No internet service'],[0,1,0],inplace=True)
df['OnlineBackup'].replace(['Yes','No','No internet service'],[1,0,0],inplace=True)
df['DeviceProtection'].replace(['No','Yes','No internet service'],[0,1,0],inplace=True)
df['TechSupport'].replace(['No','Yes','No internet service'],[0,1,0],inplace=True)
df['StreamingTV'].replace(['No','Yes','No internet service'],[0,1,0],inplace=True)
df['StreamingMovies'].replace(['No','Yes','No internet service'],[0,1,0],inplace=True)
df['Contract'].replace(['Month-to-month','One year','Two year'],[0,1,2],inplace=True)
df['PaperlessBilling'].replace(['Yes','No'],[1,0],inplace=True)
df['PaymentMethod'].replace(['Electronic check', 'Mailed check', 'Bank transfer (automatic)',
 'Credit card (automatic)'],[0,1,2,3],inplace=True)
df['Churn'].replace(['No','Yes'],[0,1],inplace=True)

Undersampling (Near Mess)¶

In [56]:
from collections import Counter
from imblearn.under_sampling import NearMiss
ns = NearMiss(0.8)
X_s,y_s = ns.fit_sample(X,y)

print('Original target variable dataset shape:', Counter(y))
print('target distribution after balancing:', Counter(y_s))

target distribution after balancing: Counter({0: 2336, 1: 1869})

Undersampling leads to loss of values. It is highly recomend for large dataset. Let us try with oversampling.

Oversampling (SMOTE)¶

In [58]:
from collections import Counter
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE

smote = SMOTE()

# fit target and predictor variable
X_sm , y_sm = smote.fit_sample(X, y)

print('Origianl dataset shape:',Counter(y))
print('Resampple dataset shape:',Counter(y_sm))

Origianl dataset shape: Counter({0: 5174, 1: 1869})
Resampple dataset shape: Counter({0: 5174, 1: 5174})

Conclusion and improvisation¶

conclusion¶

EDA,data visualisation,preprocessing and model building is carried out for telecom churn dataset, the following conclusion can be drawn. 1.Since, most of the independent variables are categorical in nature hence outliers are almost nill. 2.Univariate analysis has been carried out showing distribution of each attributes. 3.Bivariate analysis has been carried out showing distribution of each independent variable with respect to target variable (Churn) 4.Multivariate analysis like correlation plot has also been carried out. 5.Target variable distribution is found imbalnced, hence, undersampling(Near mess) and oversampling(SMOTE) of target variable distribution has been done. Finally considered oversampling(SMOTE)technique. 6.80% of the target variable is is considered for training and 20% for testing. 7.Model was builded for Logistic regression,SVM,KNN,Decision tree,Random forrest, bagging classifier, Ada boost and gradient boost classifier. 8.Ensembled model like Random forrest, bagging classifier, Adaboost and gradient boost classifier were also considered. 9.Training accuracy, testing accuracy(model accuracy),classification report were displayed for all the models. 10.Comaprision for all the models were made and found Gradient boost is the best model in terms of Training accuracy(84.84%), Testing accuracy(82.41%) and confusion matrix. Followed by Logistic Regression. Since, Random Forrest and Bagging classifier performing well in terms of training accuracy but it is overfitting the data.

Suggestions or improvements¶

1.The number of independent attributes like 'InternetService','OnlineSecurity','OnlineBackup' can be consolidated as single attribute like 'Interservice'. Also 'StreamingTv' and 'StreamingMovies' can also be consolidated under a single column. 2. Since, many attributes being categorical in nature has more number of uniqueness within itself that could be avoided. 3.Target variable distribution is not balanced. Balancing yields loss in the data. Hence, if the target variable is found balancing that would have been better. 4.Some of the attributes like Onlinesecurity, Onlinebackup,DeviceProtection, TechSupport, Streaming TV and streamingMovies has uniqueness like 'Yes','No','No internet Service' that could be replaced with 'Yes' and 'No' only.
